### 1. Publish Order to Producer (Kafka)
# Run this first to send data to the system.
# Note: Ensure all services (zookeeper, kafka, producer, consumer, inventory) are running.
POST http://localhost:9080/api/v1/kafka/publish
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customerName": "John Doe",
    "items": [
        {
            "productId": 101,
            "itemName": "Laptop",
            "quantity": 1,
            "price": 1000,
            "uom": "Unit"
        },
        {
            "productId": 102,
            "itemName": "Mouse",
            "quantity": 2,
            "price": 20,
            "uom": "Unit"
        }
    ]
}

### 2. View All Orders (Consumer Service)
# This retrieves data from the Consumer's H2 database.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders

### 3. View All Inventory (Inventory Service)
# This retrieves data from the Inventory Service's H2 database.
GET http://localhost:8081/api/inventory
